Detailed Description

cvmx_bgx::_gmp_gmi_tx_ifg

Consider the following when programming IFG1 and IFG2: * For 10/100/1000 Mb/s half-duplex systems that require IEEE 802.3 compatibility, IFG1 must be in the range of 1-8, IFG2 must be in the range of 4-12, and the IFG1 + IFG2 sum must be 12. * For 10/100/1000 Mb/s full-duplex systems that require IEEE 802.3 compatibility, IFG1 must be in the range of 1-11, IFG2 must be in the range of 1-11, and the IFG1 + IFG2 sum must be 12. For all other systems, IFG1 and IFG2 can be any value in the range of 1-15, allowing for a total possible IFG sum of 2-30.
